INSERT INTO `wp_comments` VALUES (1,1,'Mr WordPress','','http://wordpress.org/','','2007-10-20 13:15:58','2007-10-20 17:15:58','Hi, this is a comment.<br />To delete a comment, just log in and view the post&#039;s comments. There you will have the option to edit or delete them.',0,'1','','',0,0),(2,91,'Alex','alex@forthehour.com','http://www.forthehour.com','75.87.116.49','2007-10-24 23:07:32','2007-10-25 03:07:32','For some reason I thought you were being sarcastic...I kept thinking that he was dishing out bags of weed... :-)',0,'1','Mozilla/5.0 (Macintosh; U; Intel Mac OS X; en-US; rv:1.8.1.8) Gecko/20071008 Firefox/2.0.0.8','',0,0),(3,91,'jessie','jess@burningones.com','http://burningones.com/','151.199.243.57','2007-10-25 00:08:40','2007-10-25 04:08:40','No, no sarcasm. Although I am worried as to why that was your first thought... :-)',0,'1','Mozilla/5.0 (Macintosh; U; PPC Mac OS X; en) AppleWebKit/419.3 (KHTML, like Gecko) Safari/419.3','',0,3),(4,98,'Timmy V.','tim@burningones.com','http://burningones.com/','74.94.48.46','2007-11-08 13:35:51','2007-11-08 17:35:51','Finally, the woman has developed a brain! ;)\r\n\r\nHaha, but seriously.  Everyone should investigate some sort of feed/news reader.  Google has one that is free and all online.  It\'s just such an awesome way to check all the websites your used to checking.',0,'1','Mozilla/5.0 (Macintosh; U; Intel Mac OS X; en-US; rv:1.8.1.9) Gecko/20071025 Firefox/2.0.0.9','',0,0),(5,97,'Timmy V.','tim@burningones.com','http://burningones.com/','74.94.48.46','2007-11-08 13:37:42','2007-11-08 17:37:42','This is so ridiculously hard...\r\n\r\nI have absolutely no idea what they would be...\r\n\r\nLord of the Rings in easily up there.  The Matrix trilogy is up there for me as well.  Those are really the only two that I\'m totally sure about...\r\n\r\nGah!',0,'1','Mozilla/5.0 (Macintosh; U; Intel Mac OS X; en-US; rv:1.8.1.9) Gecko/20071025 Firefox/2.0.0.9','',0,0),(6,102,'Alex','alex@forthehour.com','http://www.forthehour.com','75.87.116.49','2007-11-20 14:32:03','2007-11-20 18:32:03','I love how God allows us to romance with Him in and out of different seasons. He does whatever necessary to cause us to seek Him! Its like playing peek-a-boo as a little kid- He hides Himself- just so He can thrill us again! \r\n\r\nKeep going!',0,'1','Mozilla/5.0 (Macintosh; U; Intel Mac OS X; en-US; rv:1.8.1.9) Gecko/20071025 Firefox/2.0.0.9','',0,0),(7,104,'tim','tim@burningones.com','http://burningones.com/','66.7.133.193','2007-12-06 15:08:29','2007-12-06 19:08:29','Amen.',0,'1','Mozilla/5.0 (Macintosh; U; Intel Mac OS X; en-US; rv:1.8.1.11) Gecko/20071127 Firefox/2.0.0.11','',0,2),(8,109,'tim','tim@burningones.com','http://burningones.com/','199.196.144.11','2007-12-12 14:58:32','2007-12-12 18:58:32','I\'m definitely pro not following the accepted trend of politeness.  At the same time, I think that we have to love people enough to want to be polite, you know?\r\n\r\nSo, I think in the absence of love, we should act lovingly, asking God to create love in us as we create love in ourselves.  Woah... deep ;)\r\n\r\nLove ya!',0,'1','Mozilla/5.0 (Windows; U; Windows NT 5.1; en-US; rv:1.8.1.11) Gecko/20071127 Firefox/2.0.0.11','',0,2),(9,111,'Alex','alex@forthehour.com','http://www.forthehour.com','71.242.116.243','2007-12-14 16:43:37','2007-12-14 20:43:37','I think I am done researching this stuff! I cannot stand the confusion and paradox of it all. (Not to mention the paradox in my own head of wanting to be informed but without the drama of it all.) Anyway- for now, I will continue to live my life feeling confident in the fact that I am doing all I can (and feel led) to do as a steward of my environment. \r\n\r\nBut it sure is interesting...just how do you not go insane?',0,'1','Mozilla/5.0 (Macintosh; U; Intel Mac OS X; en-US; rv:1.8.1.11) Gecko/20071127 Firefox/2.0.0.11','',0,0),(10,122,'retro','retrospam@gmail.com','http://www.christiansbehaving.wordpress.com','68.82.103.132','2008-01-02 20:16:44','2008-01-03 00:16:44','Hate to be negative myself, but this thing will turn negative very quick. I can\'t believe how much pre-Iowa hype we\'ve been getting for the last month. Ugh. Reminds me of a certain SNL skit about the Bush/Gore debate... \"Lockbox...\" \"I agree...\" \"I agree...\"',0,'1','Mozilla/5.0 (Windows; U; Windows NT 6.0; en-US; rv:1.8.1.11) Gecko/20071127 Firefox/2.0.0.11','',0,0),(11,126,'2 cubes away','travis@snowpatch.net','http://www.sweetpeaflowers.com','199.196.144.11','2008-01-03 15:04:41','2008-01-03 19:04:41','\"I’m definitely not saying that I don’t have room to grow in this area\" is very funny!',0,'1','Mozilla/4.0 (compatible; MSIE 6.0; Windows NT 5.1; SV1; .NET CLR 1.1.4322)','',0,0),(12,111,'tim','tim@burningones.com','http://burningones.com/','199.196.144.12','2008-01-03 16:33:41','2008-01-03 20:33:41','I think the only way not to go insane is just to keep a level head about it all.  The way I approach the issue is with a healthy understanding that Everyone is going to have an agenda and that most reports that are overly littered with emotional appeals and such should be taken as more suspect than reports that just present that facts.  Unfortunately, that means almost all of the reports out there because as humans we just don\'t have the ability to present unspun facts.\r\n\r\nHowever, I\'m truly tired of just reading news items, I want meaty books.  Unfortunately the best recommendation that I\'ve recieved so far is to go watch An Inconvenient Truth.  Oh Well...',0,'1','Mozilla/5.0 (Windows; U; Windows NT 5.1; en-US; rv:1.8.1.11) Gecko/20071127 Firefox/2.0.0.11','',0,2),(13,122,'tim','tim@burningones.com','http://burningones.com/','199.196.144.12','2008-01-03 16:35:32','2008-01-03 20:35:32','I\'m not familiar with that skit, is it on YouTube or somewhere else on the web?\r\n\r\nI think my favorite part of the Iowa hype was when Hillary\'s supporter said that Iowa\'s special status in the preliminaries should be taken away because it was undemocratic.  Wonderful campaign blemish.  However, she did distance herself from it almost immediately.\r\n\r\n**shrugs**',0,'1','Mozilla/5.0 (Windows; U; Windows NT 5.1; en-US; rv:1.8.1.11) Gecko/20071127 Firefox/2.0.0.11','',0,2),(14,127,'retro','retrospam@gmail.com','http://www.christiansbehaving.wordpress.com','68.82.103.132','2008-01-04 13:03:37','2008-01-04 17:03:37','Not sure if you\'ve read any CHICK TRACTS, but I wonder if they were behind this. These tracts are little cartoons with a recurring emphasis on a human-looking demon who rides shotgun and encourages the driver to go through a RR crossing (\"sure you can make it!\" \"are you... CHICKEN???\"). The inevitable result is that the dude perishes with a giant YAAAAAAAAA! sound and wakes up damned and the demon takes his mask off and basically calls him a sucker. Yeah, and we wonder why people are so turned off the gospel!?! <a href=\"http://www.christiansbehaving.wordpress.com\" rel=\"nofollow\">CBB</a>',0,'1','Mozilla/5.0 (Windows; U; Windows NT 6.0; en-US; rv:1.8.1.11) Gecko/20071127 Firefox/2.0.0.11','',0,0),(15,127,'tim','tim@burningones.com','http://burningones.com/','199.196.144.13','2008-01-04 14:11:29','2008-01-04 18:11:29','I actually never had read them or even heard of them.  I Googled them and came up with <a href=\"http://www.chick.com/\" title=\"Chick Publications\" rel=\"nofollow\">their homepage</a> which has a <a href=\"http://www.chick.com/catalog/tractlist.asp\" title=\"English Tract Listing\" rel=\"nofollow\">complete listing</a> of all their current tracts I guess.  I couldn\'t find any with the railroad crossing tract, even after doing <a href=\"http://www.google.com/search?q=Chick+Tracts+railroad+crossing\" title=\"Chick Tracts search\" rel=\"nofollow\">this search</a> in an attempt to turn it up.  However, <a href=\"http://www.chick.com/reading/tracts/0086/0086_01.asp\" title=\"The Sissy?\" rel=\"nofollow\">this tract</a> should offer you a good enough introduction to their world.  I love how the two reprobate sinners are dirty and fat and scrawny, smoking and all the rest, while the born again trucker is huge and muscular with a cut jaw line who\'s simple message wins over even the waitress who has overheard him giving a message great for truckers and bikers.  Sure matches the picture of Jesus who had an appearance that would not attract men to him.\r\n\r\nAnyway, if you can find a link to that comic, I\'d love to see it.  :)',0,'1','Mozilla/5.0 (Windows; U; Windows NT 5.1; en-US; rv:1.8.1.11) Gecko/20071127 Firefox/2.0.0.11','',0,2),(16,121,'Jac','jaclyn@forthehour.com','http://Forthehour.com','75.87.116.49','2008-01-08 18:31:02','2008-01-08 22:31:02','I forgot how to blog and by the time I fixed everything I noticed it.  I didn\'t know how to change it... Oh well.  I guess Alex will take credit for that one.',0,'1','Mozilla/5.0 (Macintosh; U; PPC Mac OS X Mach-O; en-US; rv:1.8.1.11) Gecko/20071127 Firefox/2.0.0.11','',0,0),(17,129,'retro','retrospam@gmail.com','http://www.christiansbehaving.wordpress.com','68.82.103.132','2008-01-09 15:37:33','2008-01-09 19:37:33','I heard years ago that he\'s for partial-birth abortion. However, he is against the war and probably capital punishment so the religious left would probably cancel it out. <a href=\"http://www.christiansbehaving.wordpress.com\" rel=\"nofollow\">CBB</a>',0,'1','Mozilla/5.0 (Windows; U; Windows NT 6.0; en-US; rv:1.8.1.11) Gecko/20071127 Firefox/2.0.0.11','',0,0),(18,129,'tim','tim@burningones.com','http://burningones.com/','199.196.144.13','2008-01-10 11:13:03','2008-01-10 15:13:03','I was just having a conversation with one of my coworkers and I confessed that I just don\'t want to be in the position where I can\'t vote for anyone.  I think that will be the sign that the church has failed in it\'s petitioning of God to give us a Godly candidate.  If we cannot vote for anyone because of his or her stance on abortion, then I\'m troubled for the future of the U.S.  \r\n\r\nGod help us, right?',0,'1','Mozilla/5.0 (Windows; U; Windows NT 5.1; en-US; rv:1.8.1.11) Gecko/20071127 Firefox/2.0.0.11','',0,2),(19,129,'Jac','jaclyn@forthehour.com','http://Forthehour.com','75.87.116.49','2008-01-12 13:48:29','2008-01-12 17:48:29','http://www.ontheissues.org/Barack_Obama.htm\r\n\r\nYou can go to that website.  That\'s what I found.',0,'1','Mozilla/5.0 (Macintosh; U; PPC Mac OS X Mach-O; en-US; rv:1.8.1.11) Gecko/20071127 Firefox/2.0.0.11','',0,0),(20,135,'retro','retrospam@gmail.com','http://www.christiansbehaving.wordpress.com','68.82.103.132','2008-01-15 13:09:01','2008-01-15 18:09:01','I am still livid at myspace for sending porn spam to my favorite worship leader from my account in 2006. I got to meet him after 12 years and the next month he is personally writing me to let me know someone hijacked my account. Mortifying, and although my feelings cannot be bought, if one were to assign a pain and suffering amount to this incident, it definitely caused over $681,932 worth of humiliation on my part. Know any good lawyers? That guy from Seinfeld? <a href=\"http://www.christiansbehaving.wordpress.com\" rel=\"nofollow\">CBB</a>',0,'1','Mozilla/5.0 (Windows; U; Windows NT 6.0; en-US; rv:1.8.1.11) Gecko/20071127 Firefox/2.0.0.11','',0,0),(21,135,'tim','tim@burningones.com','http://burningones.com/','199.196.144.13','2008-01-15 14:02:19','2008-01-15 19:02:19','Sounds like you\'re one person who I\'m not going to have to convince that MySpace is an utterly worthless thing. :)\r\n\r\nI remember that story, that really is awful.',0,'1','Mozilla/5.0 (Windows; U; Windows NT 5.1; en-US; rv:1.8.1.11) Gecko/20071127 Firefox/2.0.0.11','',0,2),(22,139,'jessie','jess@burningones.com','http://burningones.com/','68.163.40.161','2008-01-17 16:07:06','2008-01-17 21:07:06','We could make a monolith!!!',0,'1','Mozilla/5.0 (Macintosh; U; PPC Mac OS X; en) AppleWebKit/312.9 (KHTML, like Gecko) Safari/312.6','',0,3),(23,139,'tim','tim@burningones.com','http://burningones.com/','68.163.40.161','2008-01-18 07:08:14','2008-01-18 12:08:14','Haha, you\'re obsessed! :)\r\n\r\nBesides the moment it was realized, you\'d freak out and run away with your bowels quivering because of how scared you are of those things.',0,'1','Mozilla/5.0 (Macintosh; U; Intel Mac OS X; en-US; rv:1.8.1.11) Gecko/20071127 Firefox/2.0.0.11','',0,2),(24,151,'jessie','jess@burningones.com','http://burningones.com/','151.201.156.224','2008-02-22 08:41:42','2008-02-22 13:41:42','Wow.. I had no idea you were THIS organized! And I\'m married to you! Hehe. Sounds great!',0,'1','Mozilla/5.0 (Macintosh; U; PPC Mac OS X; en) AppleWebKit/312.9 (KHTML, like Gecko) Safari/312.6','',0,3),(25,151,'Jesse','jessejharper@gmail.com','','68.42.22.238','2008-02-25 20:45:15','2008-02-26 01:45:15','Ok, I wish you the best of luck. I will be stealing your idea in the near future, as soon as I get around to and remember to do and have enough time and can get it done fast enough. Love ya bro',0,'1','Mozilla/5.0 (Macintosh; U; PPC Mac OS X; en) AppleWebKit/523.12.2 (KHTML, like Gecko) Version/3.0.4 Safari/523.12.2','',0,0),(26,151,'tim','tim@burningones.com','http://burningones.com/','68.163.38.116','2008-02-26 05:35:11','2008-02-26 10:35:11','@Jesse: Hah!  I will need lots of luck and prayer if I\'m ever going to get this thing down, no doubt!  Thanks for your well wishes.  Don\'t fall into the trap that I fall into all the time though of hearing an idea and screwing up any progress you\'ve made because you think the idea is so cool! ;)\r\n\r\n@Jess: You had no idea because I haven\'t successfully done this yet!  It\'s still mostly on paper, though it is in my head and I\'m trying to get it working in real life.  Maybe one day you\'ll get on here and comment, \"Duh, everyone can see that you do this!\" ^_^\r\n\r\nThanks for the comments guys!\r\n\r\nTimmy V.',0,'1','Mozilla/5.0 (Macintosh; U; Intel Mac OS X; en-US; rv:1.8.1.12) Gecko/20080201 Firefox/2.0.0.12','',0,2),(27,151,'Kevin','chestnutk@chc.edu','http://none','71.224.196.200','2008-03-12 04:34:47','2008-03-12 09:34:47','Tim\r\nJust checked out your site and the article you wrote was an interesting read.  I tend to be scatterbrained and while I have plenty of good ideas and projects I want to develop; I don\'t allot the time needed to focus.  You gave a lot of insight into how a person can make themselves more efficient and with that, more productive.  Take iy Easy.',0,'1','Mozilla/4.0 (compatible; MSIE 7.0; Windows NT 5.1; .NET CLR 1.0.3705; .NET CLR 1.1.4322; Media Center PC 4.0)','',0,0),(28,163,'Alex','alex@forthehour.com','http://www.forthehour.com','75.87.116.49','2008-04-04 08:40:42','2008-04-04 13:40:42','I am loving it bro! You are on to something that many of us would write off as an over the top way to be productive in life. Being in control of your seconds in life helps us to redeem our time. And if developing a morning and nightly routine is a way to make sure that no seconds or minutes go without purpose, than go for it! I like how you have built your routine around things that can change, so that when your days look different, your routine can stay the same! I\'ll have to implement that!\r\n\r\nGood stuff!',0,'1','Mozilla/5.0 (Macintosh; U; Intel Mac OS X; en-US; rv:1.8.1.13) Gecko/20080311 Firefox/2.0.0.13','',0,0);
